The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Wednesday, June 16, 2004 				 First shower floods roads
 OUR CORRESPONDENT																								After the first heavy showers of the season on Monday night, parts of Calcutta and the surrounding areas are now under knee-deep water. 																								Pockets of south and central Calcutta, like Dhakuria, Topsia, the Dhapa lockgate, Park Street, Royd Street and Shakespeare Sarani were flooded till Tuesday evening (Picture on Page 18). 																								Mayoral council member (sewerage) Mala Roy, who visited the areas, said Topsia experienced 42 mm of rain, Dhakuria about 22 mm and Dhapa areas about 42 mm. 																								Contaminated water from the leather factories has inundated the Topsia-Tiljala belt.
